      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form selection must be justified by physics arguments and supported by literature; nonlinear material and contact formulations required for pedicle screw constructs.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity with experimentally measured Ti-6Al-4V stress-strain data is used for screw and rod. Frictional contact (mu=0.3) at screw-rod and rod-block interfaces is justified by prior cadaveric and bench literature. Model form is appropriate for the COU."
