      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test specimens must be production-representative; sample size sufficient to characterize variability; traceability to lot records required.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs assembled from production-lot components. Lot traceability confirmed. Specimen-to-specimen variability in stiffness CV=4.1%, consistent with expected manufacturing variability. Sample size adequate for E/uval metric."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions must replicate ASTM F1717 protocol; environmental conditions and loading rate documented; multiple laboratories preferred.",
      "rationale": "ASTM F1717 protocol followed at two independent laboratories. However, only a single loading rate (5 mm/min) was evaluated; the influence of loading rate on quasi-static response was not independently varied. This limits the achieved level to 2, below the required level of 3. This gap is accepted given the quasi-static nature of the COU and the consistency across laboratories."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model input parameters must be demonstrably equivalent to test specimen parameters; geometry, material, and boundary conditions matched.",
      "rationale": "CMM-measured specimen geometry was used to individualize each of the 11 FEA model instances. Material properties assigned from the same production lot as test specimens. Boundary conditions replicate the F1717 fixture geometry and constraints. Equivalency confirmed by parameter-by-parameter comparison table."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
